<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT #1 OF KIMBERLY HILL</TI>
<P>I, Kimberly Hill, of Suite 400&mdash;856 Homer Street, Vancouver, British Columbia, paralegal, AFFIRM THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am a paralegal with Camp Fiorante Matthews Mogerman (&ldquo;CFM&rdquo;), counsel for the plaintiffs in this matter and filed related matters, and as such I have personal knowledge of the facts deposed to in this Affidavit except where stated to be on information and belief, in which case I verily believe them to be true.</P>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Background</EM></TI>
<P>2. The Notice of Civil Claim in this action was filed on November 20, 2014, with an Amended Notice of Civil Claim being filed on May 31, 2017 (the &ldquo;<EM>Araya et al</EM> action&rdquo;). The <EM>Araya et al</EM> action named three plaintiffs and was filed as a proposed representative proceeding. The defendant, Nevsun Resources Ltd., filed an application in the British Columbia Supreme Court challenging the representative proceeding form of action. That application was granted on October 6, 2016.</P>
<P>3. Since October 6, 2016, a number of related actions have been filed against the defendant. The following nine additional actions, involving 89 additional plaintiffs, have been filed:
<P1>(a) <CASEREF><SOC>Alemayo v. Nevsun Resources Ltd.</SOC><JUDGDATE>filed October 19, 2016</JUDGDATE><DOCKET>SCBC Action No. S169522</DOCKET></CASEREF> (the &ldquo;<EM>Alemayo</EM> action&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(b) <CASEREF><SOC>Negash et al v. Nevsun Resources Ltd.</SOC><JUDGDATE>filed November 23, 2016</JUDGDATE><DOCKET>SCBC Action No. S-1610863</DOCKET></CASEREF> (the &ldquo;<EM>Negash et al</EM> action&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(c) <CASEREF><SOC>Tsegay et al v. Nevsun Resources Ltd.</SOC><JUDGDATE>filed February 16, 2017</JUDGDATE><DOCKET>SCBC Action No. S171414</DOCKET></CASEREF> (the &ldquo;<EM>Tsegay et al</EM> action&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(d) <CASEREF><SOC>Berhe et al v. Nevsun Resources Ltd.</SOC><JUDGDATE>filed May 23, 2017</JUDGDATE><DOCKET>SCBC Action No. S-174850</DOCKET></CASEREF> (the &ldquo;<EM>Berhe et al</EM> action&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(e) <CASEREF><SOC>Hadish v. Nevsun Resources Ltd.</SOC><JUDGDATE>filed May 23, 2017</JUDGDATE><DOCKET>SCBC Action No. S-174851</DOCKET></CASEREF> (the &ldquo;<EM>Hadish action</EM>&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(f) <CASEREF><SOC>Fshaye et al v. Nevsun Resources Ltd.</SOC><JUDGDATE>filed November 17, 2017</JUDGDATE><DOCKET>SCBC Action No. S-1710736</DOCKET></CASEREF> (the &ldquo;<EM>Fshaye et al</EM> action&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(g) <CASEREF><SOC>Hailemichael v. Nevsun Resources Ltd.</SOC><JUDGDATE>filed December 22, 2017</JUDGDATE><DOCKET>SCBC Action No. S1711866</DOCKET></CASEREF> (the &ldquo;<EM>Hailemichael</EM> action&rdquo;);</P1>
<P1>(h) <CASEREF><SOC>Mekonen et al v. Nevsun Resources Ltd.</SOC><JUDGDATE>filed March 26, 2018</JUDGDATE><DOCKET>SCBC Action No. S-184108</DOCKET></CASEREF> (the &ldquo;<EM>Mekonen et al</EM> action&rdquo;); and</P1>
<P1>(i) <CASEREF><SOC>Mohemmed-Adem et al v. Nevsun Resources Ltd.</SOC><JUDGDATE>filed May 24, 2018</JUDGDATE><DOCKET>SCBC Action No. S186035</DOCKET></CASEREF> (the &ldquo;<EM>Mohemmed-Adem et al</EM> action&rdquo;).</P1>
<P1>(collectively including the <EM>Araya et al</EM> action, the &ldquo;Actions&rdquo;)</P1></P>
<P>4. The Actions are under the common judicial management of the Honourable Mr. Justice Abrioux.</P>
<P>5. On May 15, 2018, plaintiffs' counsel filed a Notice of Discontinuance pertaining to the claim of Isias Desta, a plaintiff in the <EM>Negash et al</EM> action.</P>
<P>6. On June 7, 2018, plaintiffs' counsel filed a Notice of Discontinuance pertaining to the claim of Yakob Abreham, a plaintiff in the <EM>Tsegay et al</EM> action.</P>
<P>7. On September 20, 2018, plaintiffs' counsel filed Notices of Discontinuance pertaining to the claims of Ghirmay Teklezgi, a plaintiff in the <EM>Negash et al</EM> action, and Habtemariam Kifle, a plaintiff in the <EM>Mekenon et al</EM> action.</P>
<P>8. On October 22, 2018, plaintiffs' counsel filed a Notice of Discontinuance pertaining to the claim of Habtom Gaiem, a plaintiff in the <EM>Negash et al</EM> action.</P>
<P>9. On December 5, 2018, plaintiffs' counsel filed a Notice of Discontinuance pertaining to the claim of Solomon Mahdere, a plaintiff in the <EM>Tsegay et al</EM> action.</P>
<P>10. On January 4, 2019, plaintiffs' counsel filed a Notice of Discontinuance pertaining to the claim of Temesgen Redae, a plaintiff in the <EM>Negash</EM> action.</P>
<P>11. As at the time of affirming this Affidavit, there are 85 plaintiffs proceeding with claims against the defendant in the Actions.</P>
<P>12. A trial has been scheduled in the <EM>Araya et al</EM> action for six months commencing April 6, 2020.</P></BLOCK2>
<BLOCK2><TI><EM>Defendant's Application</EM></TI>
<P>13. On December 19, 2018, the defendant filed an application alleging that by pleading postponement, the plaintiffs in each of the Actions had waived privilege over solicitor-client communications (the &ldquo;Waiver Application&rdquo;).</P>
<P>14. The Waiver Application was heard before Mr. Justice Abrioux on January 10 and 11, 2019.</P>
<P>15. I am informed by Mr. Jamie Thornback, counsel for the plaintiffs, that Mr. Justice Abrioux delivered oral reasons at hearing on January 18, 2019. I am further informed by Mr. Thornback that Mr. Justice Abrioux advised counsel that written reasons would follow.</P>
<P>16. As of the date of affirming this Affidavit written reason for judgment have not been released.</P>
