<BLOCK1><TI>ORDER OF A JUSTICE</TI>
<P>BEFORE THE HONOURABLE MR. JUSTICE G. BRUCE BUTLER IN CHAMBERS.</P>
<P>Vancouver, British Columbia, Friday, the 22nd day of March, 2019.</P>
<P>THE APPLICATION OF THE APPELLANTS, Gize Yebeyo Araya, Kesete Tekle Fshazion and Mihretab Yemane Tekle, for an order that the Notice of Application for Leave to Appeal stand as a Notice of Appeal or alternatively leave to appeal, and for a stay of execution pending appeal, conning on for hearing the 18th day of March 2019 at Vancouver, British Columbia; AND ON HEARING Reidar M. Mogerman and Katie I. Duke, counsel for the appellants; and Andrew I. Nathanson, Tom A. Posyniak and Rachel E. Schechter, counsel for the respondent; AND ON READING the materials filed herein; AND ON JUDGMENT BEING PRONOUNCED ON THIS DATE;</P>
<P>IT IS ORDERED THAT the Notice of Application for Leave to Appeal in this proceeding stands as a Notice of Appeal of the order of Mr. Justice Abrioux of the Supreme Court of British Columbia, pronounced the 18th day of January, 2019 (the &ldquo;Order&rdquo;);</P>
<P>IT IS FURTHER ORDERED THAT execution of the Order is stayed pending determination of the appeal of the Order;</P>
<P>IT IS FURTHER ORDERED THAT the appeal of the Order is expedited;</P>
<P>IT IS FURTHER ORDERED THAT the parties file and serve documents for the appeal according to the following schedule:
<P1>(a) the appellants are to file and serve the appeal record on or before April 5, 2019;</P1>
<P1>(b) the appellants are to file and serve their appeal book(s) and factum on or before April 19, 2019;</P1>
<P1>(c) the appellants are to file and serve the certificate of readiness and notice of hearing after the filing of their factum, at the latest;</P1>
<P1>(d) the respondent is to file and serve its appeal book(s) and factum on or before May 3, 2019;</P1>
<P1>(e) the appellants are to file and serve their reply factum on or before May 8, 2019; and</P1>
<P1>(f) the parties are to file a joint book of authorities on or before May 10, 2019.</P1></P>
<P>2. IT IS FURTHER ORDERED THAT the appeal be heard on May 17, 2019.</P>
<P>3. IT IS FURTHER ORDERED THAT costs of this application are in the cause of the appeal of the Order.</P>
